    Let invalid_code be "let = 42"  Note: Missing identifier
    Let tokens be proc tokenize_fsharp from FSharpLexer with invalid_code
    Let ast be proc parse_fsharp_source from FSharpParser with tokens

    Note: Should handle gracefully - either return partial AST or null
    Return 1  Note: Accept any reasonable error handling behavior
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: Performance Tests
Note: ============================================================================

@Reasoning:
Performance test verifying the full pipeline runs on a large
generated F# source within reasonable bounds.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Build a large F# source via generate_large_fsharp_code_sample, run
the full pipeline, assert it completes without error.
@End Implementation

@TestCases:
- Large input -> pipeline completes, passed
- Pipeline times out or errors -> failure
@End TestCases

Process called "test_fsharp_large_file_performance" takes suite as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Test F# translation performance on large files

    Note: Generate large F# code sample
    Let large_code be proc generate_large_fsharp_code_sample

    Note: Time the translation process
    Let start_time be proc get_time_us from SystemInfo

    Let tokens be proc tokenize_fsharp from FSharpLexer with large_code
    Let ast be proc parse_fsharp_source from FSharpParser with tokens
    Let hir be proc translate_fsharp_to_hir from FSharpToHIR with ast
    Let generated_code be proc generate_fsharp_code from HIRToFSharp with hir

    Let end_time be proc get_time_us from SystemInfo
    Let elapsed_time be end_time minus start_time

    Display "Large file translation took: " continuing
    Display elapsed_time continuing
    Display "us"

    proc assert_not_null with suite, generated_code, "Large file translation should succeed"

    Return 1
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: Test Helper Functions
Note: ============================================================================

@Reasoning:
Helper that synthesizes a large F# source string for the performance
test. Generates representative code with N let bindings, functions,
and record types.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Build a string by concatenating template fragments enough times to
produce a sizable workload for the pipeline. Returns the resulting
string pointer.
@End Implementation

Process called "generate_large_fsharp_code_sample" returns Integer:
    Note: Generate a large F# code sample for performance testing

    Let code be proc stringbuilder_create from StringBuilder

    proc stringbuilder_append from StringBuilder with code, "module LargeTestModule =\n\n"

    Let i be 0
    While i is less than 100:
        proc stringbuilder_append from StringBuilder with code, "    let func"
        proc stringbuilder_append_integer from StringBuilder with code, i
        proc stringbuilder_append from StringBuilder with code, " x = x + "
        proc stringbuilder_append_integer from StringBuilder with code, i
        proc stringbuilder_append from StringBuilder with code, "\n"

        Set i to i plus 1
    End While

    proc stringbuilder_append from StringBuilder with code, "\n    let testList = ["

    Set i to 0
    While i is less than 1000:
        If i is greater than 0:
            proc stringbuilder_append from StringBuilder with code, "; "
        End If
        proc stringbuilder_append_integer from StringBuilder with code, i
        Set i to i plus 1
    End While

    proc stringbuilder_append from StringBuilder with code, "]\n"

    Let result be proc stringbuilder_to_string from StringBuilder with code
    proc stringbuilder_destroy from StringBuilder with code
    Return result
End Process

@Reasoning:
Helper that produces a representative HIR function node for the emitter
tests. The old hand-rolled HIR builder API (create_hir_function_definition,
set_hir_function_name, create_hir_parameter, create_hir_binary_operation,
set_hir_binary_left/right, set_hir_function_body) no longer exists; the
real current equivalent for "give me a function HIR" is to run the actual
F# frontend pipeline over a one-line function definition. This preserves
the test's intent (feed the emitter a genuine function HIR) while using
only functions that exist today.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Lex + parse + translate the source "let add x y = x + y" through the real
F# frontend (FSharpLexer.tokenize_fsharp -> FSharpParser.parse_fsharp_source
-> FSharpToHIR.translate_fsharp_to_hir) and return the resulting HIR node.
@End Implementation

Process called "create_test_hir_function" returns Integer:
    Note: Build a function HIR node via the real F# frontend pipeline

    Let source_code be "let add x y = x + y"
    Let tokens be proc tokenize_fsharp from FSharpLexer with source_code
    Let ast be proc parse_fsharp_source from FSharpParser with tokens
    Let hir be proc translate_fsharp_to_hir from FSharpToHIR with ast
    Return hir
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: Main Test Suite Runner
Note: ============================================================================

@Reasoning:
Top-level F# test orchestrator. Creates the FSharpTestSuite,
dispatches through run_test for each phase's test_* procs (5 lexer
tests, 7 parser tests, 3 to-HIR, 2 from-HIR, 3 round-trip, 2 error
handling, 1 performance), prints results, and returns the all-pass
signal.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
1. create_fsharp_test_suite -> suite. If null, fail.
2. For each of the ~23 test_* procs, call run_test(suite,
   name_literal, test_proc_handle).
3. Print Total/Passed/Failed counts.
4. destroy_fsharp_test_suite(suite).
5. Return 1 if failed_count == 0 else 0.
@End Implementation

@TestCases:
- All sub-tests pass -> returns 1 with "ALL PASSED" message
- Any sub-test fails -> returns 0 with "SOME FAILED" message
@End TestCases

Process called "run_fsharp_test_suite" returns Integer:
    Note: Run complete F# test suite

    @Reasoning:
    This function executes all F# translation tests systematically,
    providing comprehensive coverage of the F# Translation component.
    It reports results and provides detailed feedback on any failures.
    @End Reasoning

    Let suite be proc create_fsharp_test_suite

    If suite is equal to 0:
        Display "Failed to create test suite"
        Return 0
    End If

    Display "=== F# Translation Test Suite ==="
    Display ""

    Note: Lexer Tests
    Display "--- Lexer Tests ---"
    proc run_test with suite, "Lexer Basic", proc test_fsharp_lexer_basic with suite
    proc run_test with suite, "Lexer Keywords", proc test_fsharp_lexer_keywords with suite
    proc run_test with suite, "Lexer Operators", proc test_fsharp_lexer_operators with suite
    proc run_test with suite, "Lexer Literals", proc test_fsharp_lexer_literals with suite
    proc run_test with suite, "Lexer Delimiters", proc test_fsharp_lexer_delimiters with suite

    Note: Parser Tests
    Display ""
    Display "--- Parser Tests ---"
    proc run_test with suite, "Parser Basic", proc test_fsharp_parser_basic with suite
    proc run_test with suite, "Parser Function", proc test_fsharp_parser_function with suite
    proc run_test with suite, "Parser Lambda", proc test_fsharp_parser_lambda with suite
    proc run_test with suite, "Parser Match", proc test_fsharp_parser_match with suite
    proc run_test with suite, "Parser Pipeline", proc test_fsharp_parser_pipeline with suite
    proc run_test with suite, "Parser List", proc test_fsharp_parser_list with suite
    proc run_test with suite, "Parser Record", proc test_fsharp_parser_record with suite

    Note: Translation Tests
    Display ""
    Display "--- Translation Tests ---"
    proc run_test with suite, "F# to HIR Basic", proc test_fsharp_to_hir_basic with suite
    proc run_test with suite, "F# to HIR Function", proc test_fsharp_to_hir_function with suite
    proc run_test with suite, "F# to HIR Match", proc test_fsharp_to_hir_match with suite

    Note: Code Generation Tests
    Display ""
    Display "--- Code Generation Tests ---"
    proc run_test with suite, "HIR to F# Basic", proc test_hir_to_fsharp_basic with suite
    proc run_test with suite, "HIR to F# Function", proc test_hir_to_fsharp_function with suite

    Note: Round-trip Tests
    Display ""
    Display "--- Round-trip Tests ---"
    proc run_test with suite, "Round-trip Basic", proc test_fsharp_roundtrip_basic with suite
    proc run_test with suite, "Round-trip Function", proc test_fsharp_roundtrip_function with suite
    proc run_test with suite, "Round-trip Complex", proc test_fsharp_roundtrip_complex with suite

    Note: Error Handling Tests
    Display ""
    Display "--- Error Handling Tests ---"
    proc run_test with suite, "Lexer Error Handling", proc test_fsharp_lexer_error_handling with suite
    proc run_test with suite, "Parser Error Handling", proc test_fsharp_parser_error_handling with suite

    Note: Performance Tests
    Display ""
    Display "--- Performance Tests ---"
    proc run_test with suite, "Large File Performance", proc test_fsharp_large_file_performance with suite

    Note: Print results
    Display ""
    Display "=== Test Results ==="

    Let test_count be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with suite, 0
    Let passed_count be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with suite, 8
    Let failed_count be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with suite, 16

    Let test_count_str be proc integer_to_string from StringUtils with test_count
    Let passed_count_str be proc integer_to_string from StringUtils with passed_count
    Let failed_count_str be proc integer_to_string from StringUtils with failed_count
    Display "Total tests: " joined with test_count_str

    Display "Passed: " joined with passed_count_str

    Display "Failed: " joined with failed_count_str

    If failed_count is equal to 0:
        Display ""
        Display "All tests PASSED! ✓"
    Otherwise:
        Display ""
        Display "Some tests FAILED! ✗"
    End If

    Let success be failed_count is equal to 0
    proc destroy_fsharp_test_suite with suite

    If success is equal to 1:
        Return 1
    Otherwise:
        Return 0
    End If
End Process

